# Backend Rules

## Layered architecture

```
routes → controllers → services → Prisma/DB
```

No business logic in route handlers. Follow existing files in each layer.

## API

- All routes under `/api/v1/` prefix
- Swagger via `swagger-jsdoc` + `swagger-ui-express`
- Validate all user input with Zod/schema on the backend — no exceptions
- Structured error responses from services; try-catch with descriptive messages

## Modules

- ES modules only (`import`/`export`) — no `require()`
- For `__dirname`: `fileURLToPath(import.meta.url)` + `dirname()`
- Env vars from `.env` — never hardcode credentials

## Auth

- Keycloak token validation middleware on every protected route
- Realm: `military-lms`, client: `military-lms-app`
